    "body": "@dopykuh if you're able to try it out, does inserting a `stub.instance_variable_get(\"@ch\").close` after each loop iteration fix this?\r\n\r\n(Each stub wraps a \"channel\", which holds scarce resources. Without explicitly closing it, things are only released by garbage collection. )\r\n\r\n`close` hasn't been exposed yet on the stub, but it would probably help situations like this."
