    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@dopykuh  is the question of whether it's safe to reuse a stub across calls?\r\n\r\nAlso a note on usage though: though a `close` method should probably be added to the stub for explicitly releasing resources, in general a \"channel\" (wrapped by a \"stub\"), is a somewhat heavyweight object. They <i>should</i> be reused across multiple calls if possible, as there's (roughly) effectively an http2 connection per channel."
